He said German reunification cannot go ahead of the reunification of Europe. A reported surge in anti-Polish sentiment in East Germany in recent weeks has heightened Polish anxieties. The territory is about one-third of present-day Poland. The government on Thursday allowed for the possibility of a reunified Germany, but said such a state must be formed gradually and respect Poland's borders. Some right-wing West German politicians have called for recovering the 40000 square miles of territory that Germany lost to Poland at the end of World War II. 